Who's News:
   GE's Financial Unit
   Taps Berger for Post
Mr. Berger will be responsible for a number of businesses,
including GE Capital's corporate finance group, General
Electric Railcar Service Corp., Transport International Pool,
and the Gelco Space business, as well as FGIC.
   Ann C. Stern, 39, was named president and chief executive
of FGIC, succeeding Mr. Berger. She was managing director and
general counsel and joined FGIC in 1984 as vice president,
general counsel and secretary.
   Ms. Stern said she will seek to "involve more people in
the company in more aspects of decision-making," as well as
maintain the unit's capital strength, profitability and
market share.